-- Pimco Total Return posts $4.3 bln outflows in May - Morningstar
-- By Sam Forgione
-- Mon Jun 02, 2014 04:09PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, June 2 (Reuters) - The Pimco Total Return Fund, the world's largest bond fund run by Bill Gross, posted $4.3 billion in net outflows in May, marking the 13th straight month of outflows from the fund, Morningstar data showed on Monday.

The fund had $229 billion in assets at the end of May, the data showed. The Pimco Total Return Exchange-Traded Fund <BOND.P> posted $10.8 million in net outflows in May, according to the data. That also marked the 13th straight month of outflows from the ETF.